text: Xenorhabdus hominickii is a bacterium from the genus of Xenorhabdus which has been isolated from the nematodes Steinernema karii in Kenya and Steinernema monticolum from Korea.UniProtDeutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen und Zellkulturen == References == == Further reading == * * ==External links== *Type strain of Xenorhabdus hominickii at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase Category:Bacteria described in 2006
title: Xenorhabdus hominickii
